---
import LegalLayout from "@/components/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import LegalContact from "@/components/legal/LegalContact.astro";
import { createUrl } from "@/utils/url";
import { LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED, siteData } from "@/data/content";
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="The rules governing access to and use of the public AUXO Data Labs website, its content, and related public-facing tools."
  lastUpdated={LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED}
>
  <div class="legal-callout">
    <p>
      <strong>Site terms only.</strong> These terms govern use of the public
      website. Paid services, deliverables, and client data handling are
      governed by separate signed agreements.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Acceptance of These Terms</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms of Use govern your access to and use of
    <strong>auxodata.com</strong> and related public content made available by
    AUXO Data Labs. By using the site, you agree to these Terms and to the
    related <a href={createUrl("legal/privacy-policy")}>Privacy Policy</a> and
    <a href={createUrl("legal/cookie-policy")}>Cookie Policy</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you do not agree, do not use the site.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Who Operates the Site</h2>
  <p>
    The site is owned and operated by <strong>Rapple International FZE</strong>,
    trading as AUXO Data Labs.
  </p>
  <p>
    Location: {siteData.address.street}, {siteData.address.city},{" "}
    {siteData.address.country}
  </p>
  <p>
    Contact: <a href={`mailto:${siteData.email}`}>{siteData.email}</a>
  </p>

  <h2>3. Permitted Use</h2>
  <p>
    You may use the site for lawful informational and business purposes only.
    You agree not to misuse the site, interfere with its operation, or use it
    in a way that violates applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Prohibited Conduct</h2>
  <p>
    You must not:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>attempt unauthorised access to the site, its infrastructure, or connected systems;</li>
    <li>introduce malware, malicious code, or abusive traffic;</li>
    <li>copy, republish, or exploit site content beyond ordinary internal review without permission;</li>
    <li>use bots, scrapers, spiders, or automated extraction tools to harvest site content or metadata without written approval;</li>
    <li>use site materials to train or benchmark machine-learning systems where that use would breach these Terms or applicable law;</li>
    <li>misrepresent your identity or use the site to send deceptive or unlawful communications.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>
    The site and its contents, including text, design, graphics, branding,
    layouts, code, and other materials, are owned by AUXO Data Labs or its
    licensors and protected by applicable intellectual-property laws.
  </p>
  <p>
    Except as permitted by law, you may not reproduce, distribute, modify,
    create derivative works from, publicly display, or commercially exploit
    site content without prior written consent.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Informational Content Only</h2>
  <p>
    The public site is provided for general information about AUXO, its
    services, ideas, and point of view. Nothing on the site constitutes legal,
    investment, accounting, or other regulated professional advice, and site
    content is not a substitute for a signed statement of work or formal
    engagement.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Contact Forms, Meeting Links, and Feedback</h2>
  <p>
    If you submit a message, request a meeting, or send feedback through the
    site, you are responsible for the accuracy of the information you provide.
  </p>
  <p>
    Unless we agree otherwise in writing, unsolicited feedback may be used by
    AUXO without restriction or compensation, provided that doing so does not
    override rights you retain under applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Third-Party Services and Links</h2>
  <p>
    The site may link to third-party services or embed third-party tools, such
    as external scheduling flows. Those third parties control their own
    services, terms, and privacy practices. AUXO is not responsible for
    third-party content or policies.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Availability and Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update, suspend, withdraw, or change any part of the site at any
    time, without guaranteeing uninterrupted availability or permanent access to
    any specific page, feature, or resource.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
  <p>
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, the site is provided
    <strong>"as is"</strong> and <strong>"as available"</strong>. We disclaim
    warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
    non-infringement, availability, accuracy, and security, except where such
    disclaimers are not allowed by law.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, AUXO Data Labs and its affiliates,
    officers, employees, and representatives will not be liable for indirect,
    incidental, consequential, special, exemplary, or punitive damages, or for
    loss of revenue, profits, business opportunity, goodwill, or data arising
    out of or related to your use of the site.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Indemnity</h2>
  <p>
    You agree to indemnify and hold AUXO harmless from claims, losses,
    liabilities, and expenses arising from your misuse of the site, your breach
    of these Terms, or your violation of applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Separate Client Agreements</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms do not replace any master services agreement, statement of
    work, confidentiality agreement, or other contract signed between AUXO and
    a client. If there is a conflict, the signed client agreement controls.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Governing Law</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of the United Arab Emirates. Unless
    mandatory law requires otherwise, disputes relating to these Terms or the
    site will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Dubai,
    United Arab Emirates.
  </p>

  <h2>15. Changes to These Terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may revise these Terms from time to time. The updated version will appear
    on this page with a revised last-updated date. Continued use of the site
    after changes take effect means you accept the revised Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>16. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these Terms can be sent to
    <a href={`mailto:${siteData.email}`}>{siteData.email}</a>.
  </p>

  <LegalContact
    title="Terms Contact"
    intro="For questions about site usage, licensing, or these Terms of Use, contact:"
    email={siteData.email}
  />
</LegalLayout>
